<p>This cross-Okunikko route links the rustic Kotoku Onsen hamlet with Yumoto Onsen by way of Yudaki Falls. The path climbs gradually through cedar forest before breaking out onto the Senjōgahara marshland boardwalks, where wide-open views stretch toward Mount Nantai and the surrounding peaks.</p>

<p>After skirting the base of Yudaki, the trail continues along Lake Yunoko&apos;s edge to reach the steaming baths of Yumoto Onsen. Hikers often finish with a restorative soak in one of the public hot springs or foot baths near the bus terminal.</p>

